In addition to this, we provide a case study applying this approach to the DynAIRx project. In this case study we provide details of how to apply the framework in practice. We also provide evaluation of the development process which show the benefit of automation, strategies for having efficient clinical meetings, and a comparison against other contemporary codelists in the multimorbidity area. We conclude that by applying the proposed framework, a codelist of approximately \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
